metadata.name: NEMA #7
metadata.description:
Unlike us, 
They are minimalist. 
They don't bear the stuff that are not necessary for their life.
They are easily satisfied, not materialistic at all.
They can be both father and mother. and they focus on the next generations.

They are well even when they are alone or with others.
I knew nema 27 yrs ago in my year 1 bio-diversity class.
To celebrate this friendship, I challenge myself to draw nema with only circle() and arc().

100 selected compositions with 1/2/3/4/5 nema-combo. 

Hope you like them as I do.

<S> to export the image
Best experience in large display window.

Built w/ P5js and 10% donation to P5 foundation

metadata.name: Pobbles #156
metadata.description:
The pobbles are generative blob-rocks: staring in silence, sometimes half-smiling, generally bored. 

‚Ä¢ The pobbles are digital recreations of a series of rock-doodles by S.F.Kislev (my big brother). They are an attempt to capture a specific, singular handwriting, and evolve it using code. 
‚Ä¢ See the original, 2014 handmade version here - https://pobbles.tez.page..
‚Ä¢ Alternative titles considered include Peggles‚Ñ¢, Plops‚Ñ¢, Blobbies‚Ñ¢, Floofs‚Ñ¢, Flintstones‚Ñ¢, Lardies‚Ñ¢, Plumps‚Ñ¢, Fats‚Ñ¢ and Wet-Ones‚Ñ¢. 
‚Ä¢ The pobbles are written entirely in paper.js and p5.js. 
‚Ä¢ The pobbles are an effort to take generative art into the realm of the cute. 
‚Ä¢ They work well with toddlers.

metadata.name: Frost's Road #121
metadata.description:
Do you take the less traveled road and dispel the wonder of what might have been?  Or, do you preserve the mystery by gazing down the overgrown, winding path savoring the speculation--never to be disappointed or have your wonder sated?

Frost's Road celebrates the obvious and enigmatic themes of Frost's poem, "The Road Not Taken."  A generative path to nowhere? Or someplace special?  Frost's Road subtly captures the obviousness of a vacant path, and the questions that lingers about why is that.

Created with p5js.

Press the Down Arrow to save the frame as a png.
Click or tap the canvas to toggle full screen mode.
Output Size: 995 x 1080.

metadata.name: Pobbles #87
metadata.description:
The pobbles are generative blob-rocks: staring in silence, sometimes half-smiling, generally bored. 

‚Ä¢ The pobbles are digital recreations of a series of rock-doodles by S.F.Kislev (my big brother). They are an attempt to capture a specific, singular handwriting, and evolve it using code. 
‚Ä¢ See the original, 2014 handmade version here - https://pobbles.tez.page..
‚Ä¢ Alternative titles considered include Peggles‚Ñ¢, Plops‚Ñ¢, Blobbies‚Ñ¢, Floofs‚Ñ¢, Flintstones‚Ñ¢, Lardies‚Ñ¢, Plumps‚Ñ¢, Fats‚Ñ¢ and Wet-Ones‚Ñ¢. 
‚Ä¢ The pobbles are written entirely in paper.js and p5.js. 
‚Ä¢ The pobbles are an effort to take generative art into the realm of the cute.

metadata.name: I Stockpile Dreams With Tragedies #12
metadata.description:
"I Stockpile Dreams With Tragedies" is an experimental generative art piece that is an attempt to highlight some of the inherent contradictions surrounding the discussion of non-fungible tokens (NFTs) and it's place as a vehicle for artistic creation, artistic expression and the potential of remuneration for artists.

To the extent possible, the source code is dedicated to the public domain (CC0) and can be used for any purpose, even commercial, by anyone. Third party libraries are used that are not CC0 licensed but have libre/free licensing terms that allow for commercial reuse (please see the LICENSE section for more details).

This work is heavily based on stock art that is available from pay-to-download sites and other artists that copy the style but don't release the art, or the code to generate it, to the community at large.

This work hopes to add to the conversation about examining the reality of the ecosystem that we've developed around digital goods and intellectual property.
